There are many machines on the farm and many attachments. These are some of the more important ones.
{Tractors.}
Mr Price has six tractors. One is thirty years old. It hasn't a cab for the driver or a cover for the engine. It is smaller than the new ones. The modern ones are bigger, more powerful, and more comfortable. They have many electical controls as well as hydraulic and mechanical ones. The tractor is the modern horse.
{Attachments.}
We saw a tractor with a double spike at the front lifting large, round bales of straw from a trailer onto a stack.
